<p><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif width=5><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/headers/current_affairs.gif><center><table width=100%><tr><td background=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/horizon_line.gif><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=16></td></tr></table><p><table Border=0 Bgcolor=#181818 Width=100%>
<tr><td colspan=2 Bgcolor=#000000 Align=center><font color=white size=+2>Raiding Wizards</font>
</td></tr><tr><td width=10% Bgcolor=#101010 Align=center Valign=top><table width=200><tr><td align=center><font size=-1><table><tr><td align=center><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_top.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_left.jpg><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/portraits/LUMELIENU.jpg width="104" height="184"><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_right.jpg><br clear=all><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/border_bottom.jpg></td></tr></table>Legendary  LUMELIENU<br>Level 65 Wizard<br><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_12.gif" title="Golden Order of Leadership"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif" title="Order of Meritorious Service"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif" title="Star of Achievement"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_1.gif" title="Service Cross"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_17.gif" title="Crusaders Sword"><img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_2.gif" title="Medal of Honor"><br>Webmaster<br><a style="text-decoration:none;" href="main.cgi?fetch=LUMELIENU"><font size=-1 color="#DDDDDD">LUMELIENU</font></a><font size=-1>'S LINEAGE</font><br><img src='http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/bio.gif' border=0></font></td></tr></table></td><td width=90% Valign=top><a href=main.cgi?followup=7&forum=9><p align=right><font color=#cccccc>Reply | </a><a href=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/guild-builder/call/main.cgi?action=messages&forum=9><font color=#cccccc>Return</a></p><br clear=all><p><i>Wizards can be a very beneficial addition to any raid if they know how to play their class correctly. A few basic of raiding with wizards.<br><br>1. Porting - if possible be available 30-40 min before raid starts, so you can start getting people to the meeting place. Choose an easy access location such as PoK or Nexus for pick-ups. Try to get full groups for porting, fewer trips=faster pick-ups.<br><br>2. Be prepared - Look-up what mobs we are going after, know their strengths and weaknesses. Such as Vindi is an ice giant which means he is very resistant to cold spells. So don't try and cast Draught of Ice or Ice Comet on him, it's a waste of mana. Always keep your sheilds up. Manashield will save your ass over and over and over. Make sure you have all gems, food, TL shards, etc. before you start porting.<br><br>3. Agro handling - Raids are dependant on keeping the agro on the right person. With wizards dropping the same dmg in 4 secs that it takes a tank to build in 1 min, it is very easy to gain agro. Concussion line of spells can help with lowering your agro, but the best way is to know when to nuke. Never nuke above 80 percent or before MA calls assist. I generally will nuke at 70, 50 and 20 percent, when using smaller nukes such as draughts, with biggers spells such as agnars or sunstrike, nuke at 60 and 25. These percentages are for used for instances such as HoT raids, when taking out one large mob such as Vindi, never nuke before 60 percent and then go all out. Wizards are invaluable for finishing off the last few percent, so you dont have to worry about gating mobs. Stun lines are also valuable for this but remember that giants and most dragons are immune to stun. Spells to keep up - root, snare, manashield, harvest, one draught, one lure, one major nuke, one stun.<br><br>4. Self-sacrafice - Wizards in no way  can be considered meatshields, but be prepared to gain agro if the MA and SA have died to help protect the clerics so they can camp. Major nukes will accomplish this pretty easily, and while you may only last a few seconds thats a few more seconds that a cleric will have. Use your judgement on this and only do this on situations you are sure will benefit from it. NEVER evac on a raid!!!!!!!!!<br><br>5. Familliars - there is no need to keep your familliar around. Call it up, type in /pet get lost and the familliar will go away but you keep the stat buff that it gives you. <br><br>6. AA's - Wizard AA's should be put into Mental Clarity, Casting Fury and Manaburn.<br><br>7. Porting out - remember that you will always be one of the last to leave on a raid. You need to always make sure that anyone who can't gate or port is out before you leave. TL's are much easier to do than ports. Don't worry about getting a group to port up to nexus just TL them all. <br><br>8. Wizard Epic - The wizard epic is probably one of the easiest to complete with help. It basically consists of three staffs. 1) Blue Crystal Staff - random drop off of Phinny in Kedge Keep. He can be killed easily with two groups and is used in several different epic quests, so you can usually find several people who want to kill him. 2) Gnarled staff - dropps of VS in KC, 2 to 3 groups. 3) Oil from Golem in Fear - 3 groups, with high lvl enchanter, once fear is broken getting golem is cake. I spent probably a total time of 1 hour of research, 1 hour of running around and probably 10 hours for camping mobs and raiding for my epic...12 hour epic is not bad. Proc is a damage absorbing shield and mana regen, does not stack with BL crack. For more info check out graffe's or allakhazam's under staff of the four.<br><br>This is all I can think of atm, but I'm sure there will be more to come. Feel free to ask me any questions you may have. No stupid questions only stupid answers.<br><br>Love,<br>Lume<br><br><br clear=all><br><font size=-2>(Edited by LUMELIENU on 8/1/2003 at 11:31a.m.)</font><br></i><br></td></tr><tr><td>
